When Apple first launched its App Store in 2009, CEO Steve Jobs promised consumers the marketplace would be "walled-garden" to third-party app approval. No app would be given the green light without rigorous review and inspection by Apple developers and product testers. Apple would keep consumers safe by making sure nothing foul or seedy got past the wall, while

